SIMPLE: fractious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fractious
<hw>Frac"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>frack</ets> forward, eager, E. <ets>freak</ets>, <ets>fridge</ets>;
or Prov. E. <ets>fratch</ets> to squabble, quarrel.]</ety> <def>Apt to
break out into a passion; apt to scold; cross; snappish; ugly; unruly;
<as>as, a <ex>fractious</ex> man; a <ex>fractious</ex>
horse.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Snappish; peevish; waspish; cross; irritable;
perverse; pettish.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Frac"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>v.</pos> --
<wf>Frac"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fractural</ent>⟦br⟧
